subsidiaryTaxRegNum.title: Subsidiary Tax Reg. Number
subsidiaryTaxRegNum.description: This field shows the tax registration number of the transaction nexus. NetSuite automatically populates this field based on the nexus lookup logic. You can override the transaction nexus and tax registration number that NetSuite automatically selects by checking the Nexus Override box. When you select a different tax registration number in the dropdown list, the corresponding nexus is automatically selected in the Nexus field.

subtotal.title: Subtotal
subtotal.description: This field shows the total of the items on this return authorization. This is the total before any discount, shipping cost, handling cost or tax is added to the order.

custbody_15699_exclude_from_ep_process.title: Exclude from Electronic Bank Payments Processing

custbody_sta_factoring_inv_not_to_cust.title: E-invoicing operator should not forward factoring eInvoice to customer

shipAddress.title: Ship To
shipAddress.description: The default shipping address autofills this field from the customer's record at Lists > Customers. To enter a different address: * Select another address in the Ship To Select field. * Select New in the Ship To Select field to enter a new billing address.

toBePrinted.title: To Be Printed
toBePrinted.description: Check this box if you want to save this in a queue of return authorization you can later chose to print. Otherwise, you can click Print below to submit and print this return authorization at once.

toBeEmailed.title: To Be Emailed
toBeEmailed.description: Check this box if you want to e-mail this return authorization. Then enter the e-mail address in the space to the right of the check box. You can enter multiple e-mail addresses by separating them with a semicolon. It is important to separate the addresses with only a semicolon, and do not include any spaces.

exchangeRate.title: Exchange Rate
exchangeRate.description: The currency's exchange rate is shown in this field. You can edit the exchange rate for this transaction only, or you can update the currency record with the exchange rate you enter here.

custbody_sta_loc_no_refno.title: Do not trigger invoice ref number

toBeFaxed.title: To Be Faxed
toBeFaxed.description: Check this box if you want to fax this transaction. Enter the fax number in the space to the right of the check box if it doesn't already appear. To fax NetSuite forms, an administrator must first set up fax service at Setup > Company > Printing, Fax and Email Preferences.

taxDetailsOverride.title: Tax Details Override
taxDetailsOverride.description: Check this box to override the tax information on the Tax Details subtab of the transaction. Only roles with at least the Edit level of the Tax Details Tab permission can override the tax details.

message.title: Customer Message
message.description: Select a customer message that will appear on the Return Authorization form. To add additional choices to this list, go to Setup > Accounting > Accounting Lists > New > Customer Message.

tranDate.title: Date
tranDate.description: The current date autofills this field. Enter or select another date if needed.

memo.title: Reason for Return
memo.description: If you wish, enter a memo to describe this return authorization. What you enter in this field will appear on reports.

custbody_baseamount_noaplica_iva.title: MX Base Amount VAT Not Apply

custbody_sta_fin_taxtotal_amount_base.title: VAT total Amount in base currency

discountRate.title: Rate
discountRate.description: NetSuite enters the rate for the discount item you selected. You can change the discount rate for this cash refund. Enter the discount as a dollar amount like 10.00, or as a percentage like 10%.

custbody_auto_send_document_nonstore.title: Basware Automatically Send E-document Non-stored from customer

custbody_custom_price_is_annual_rate.title: Custom List Rate is Annual Rate

total.title: Total
total.description: NetSuite computes the total of line items and tax and then enters it here.

tranId.title: Transaction Number
tranId.description: NetSuite increases the largest return authorization number by one. If you wish, you can type another number. The next return number will revert to the standard pattern. You can enter a maximum of 45 characters in this field.

altSalesTotal.title: Alt. Sales Total
altSalesTotal.description: The alternate sales amount total is shown here.

salesEffectiveDate.title: Sales Effective Date
salesEffectiveDate.description: You can change the sales effective date for this transaction. The sales effective date determines which commission plan and historical sales team this transaction applies to. If this return is created from a sales order, the sales effective date from the order shown in the Created From field is set by default for this return authorization.

taxRegOverride.title: Tax Registration Override
taxRegOverride.description: Check this box to override the values in the Nexus and Subsidiary Tax Reg. Number fields. Only roles with at least the Edit level of the Tax Details Tab permission can override the values that NetSuite automatically selects in these fields.

taxTotal.title: Tax
taxTotal.description: NetSuite multiplies the tax rate by the taxable total of line items and enters it here.

billAddress.title: Bill To
billAddress.description: The default billing address autofills this field from the customer's record at Lists > Relationships > Customers. To enter a different address: * Select another address in the Bill To Select field. * Select New in the Bill To Select field to enter a new billing address.

custbody_link_po_creation.title: Link to ESW PO creation Instructions

tranIsVsoeBundle.title: Transaction Is VSOE Bundle
tranIsVsoeBundle.description: Check this box to include all items added to this transaction as a VSOE bundle.

isCrossSubTransaction.title: Allow Cross-Subsidiary Customer Return
isCrossSubTransaction.description: Clear the Allow Cross-Subsidiary Returns box to allow returns to be received only from locations directly associated with the transaction subsidiary. Check the Allow Cross-Subsidiary Returns box box to allow receipt of returns to locations listed on GIR records associated with the transaction subsidiary. This box is checked with all locations included by default. The Inventory Location column and Inventory Subsidiary column show when the Allow Cross-Subsidiary Fulfillment feature is enabled. For each line item, use the To Location field to select the receiving location. This field shows these locations: * Locations directly associated with the transaction subsidiary * Locations listed on the Customer Return subtab of related GIR records

discountTotal.title: Discount Total
discountTotal.description: NetSuite enters the amount discounted on this return authorization. If this discount item is taxable, the discount is applied before taxes. If it is not taxable, the discount is applied after taxes.

otherRefNum.title: PO/Check Number
otherRefNum.description: For your customers' convenience, you can enter their purchase order number here.

zip.title: Zip
zip.description: Enter the postal code the way it should appear on all forms except checks.

addr2.title: Address 2
addr2.description: Enter an optional second address line the way it should appear on forms. For employees, customers, partners, and vendors, what you enter here autofills on forms if this address is marked default for Shipping or Billing. Enter up to 50 characters.

city.title: City
city.description: Enter the city the way it should appear on all forms except checks.

addr1.title: Address 1
addr1.description: Enter the address the way it should appear on forms. For employees, customers, partners, and vendors, what you enter here autofills on forms if this address is marked default for Shipping or Billing. Enter up to 50 characters. This field is required for the Online Bill Pay feature.

addressee.title: Addressee
addressee.description: Enter the name of the entity that should appear on the shipping label here. This name appears on the shipping label below what you enter in the Attention field.

attention.title: Attention
attention.description: Enter the name of the person to whom a shipment is addressed, as it should appear on shipping labels. This field is required for UPS Integration.

override.title: Override
override.description: Check this box to disable the free-form address text field. When this field is disabled, text entered in the other address fields does not display in the Address text field. Clear this box to allow text entered in the address component fields to appear in the free-form address text field.

state.title: State/Province
state.description: Enter your company's state or province the way it should appear on all forms except checks.

addrText.title: Address
addrText.description: The values entered in the other address fields are displayed here.

custcol_ff_sc_matching_status_inline.title: S&C Purchase order matching status code

itemDescription.title: Description
itemDescription.description: A more complete Description of the item.

unit.title: Units
unit.description: If the assembly uses Units of Measure, the base units are displayed in the Units field.

quantity.title: Quantity
quantity.description: In the Quantity to Build field, enter the number of assembly items you want to build. You cannot enter a quantity that exceeds the amount displayed in the Buildable Quantity field.
